AIM:
    To design a micromixer and analyze mixing efficiency of two fluids.
SOFTWARE REQUIRED:
    COMSOL Multiphysics
PROCEDURE:
Model Wizard:
    Select 3D
    Select Physics →
    Fluid Flow → Laminar Flow
    Transport of Diluted Species
    Click Add
    Select Study → Stationary
    Click Done
GEOMETRY 1
    Set Length unit = µm
CHANNEL DESIGN
    Create two inlet channels (Width = 50 µm, Height = 20 µm)
    Merge into a mixing channel (Length = 1000 µm)
    Click Build All
MATERIALS
    Add Material → Water (liquid)
LAMINAR FLOW
  INLET 1
        Velocity = 0.01 m/s
   INLET 2
       Velocity = 0.01 m/s
   OUTLET
Pressure = 0 Pa
TRANSPORT OF SPECIES
  Define concentration:
    Inlet 1 → Concentration = 1 mol/m³
    Inlet 2 → Concentration = 0 mol/m³
MESH
  Free Tetrahedral → Build Mesh
STUDY -Compute
  
RESULT:
    The mixing behavior and concentration distribution inside the micromixer are successfully analyzed.
